procstep.procdesc:
Per contract between Carlton County, MN and Pictometry International Corp., Pictometry flew 9", leaf off, ortho imagery across the entire county during the spring of 2015. GPS/INS processing: Data was post-processed using NGS CORS base station data. Mosaicing was performed using Pictometry software.
Carlton County provided the imagery to the Minnesota Geospatial Information Office (MnGeo) as MrSID files in Carlton County coordinates, units in feet. MnGeo staff converted the files into UTM coordinates, units in meters, and created the WMS layer.
